1.00	Hardwick,_Norfolk	Shelton and Hardwick	Shelton and Hardwick is a civil parish in South Norfolk, England made up of the villages of Shelton and Hardwick. It lies about 3 km southeast of Long Stratton, about 6 km north of Harleston and 10 km west of Bungay. It covers an area of 8.90 km2 (3.44 sq mi) and had a population of 283 in 107 households as of the 2001 census.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Hardwick-g2.jpg/240px-Hardwick-g2.jpg
